============================================================
PYTHON EDA – ANALYTICAL VISUALIZATION SUMMARY
============================================================

Description:
This script contains the exploratory data analysis (EDA)
phase of the project, using Python to analyze and visualize
the structured datasets generated from the SQL section.

While the SQL part (01, 02, and 03) focused on data extraction,
aggregation, and structuring, this script builds on those
results by transforming them into visual insights and
interpretable patterns.

The goal is to provide:
- a clear visual overview of the dataset
- an in-depth analysis of team performance
- a focused exploration of key matchups between top teams


------------------------------------------------------------
Structure of the Script
------------------------------------------------------------

The script is divided into three main parts:


01 – General Overview (04_01.csv)
Provides a high-level visualization of the dataset,
including total matches, teams, averages, and overall
distribution metrics.

This section helps establish context and validate the
dataset before deeper analysis.


02 – Team Performance Analysis (04_02.csv)
Analyzes team-level performance using multiple approaches:

- Ranking Analysis:
  Identifies top teams based on wins, win rate, goals scored,
  and goal difference.

- Comparative Analysis:
  Examines differences between home and away performance.

- Relationship Analysis:
  Uses scatter plots to explore connections between key
  variables such as goals, goal difference, and win rate.

- Correlation Analysis:
  Uses heatmaps to identify relationships between performance
  metrics and understand how team statistics interact.

This section provides a complete performance profile
for each team.


03 – Big 5 Matchup Analysis (04_03.csv)
Focuses on head-to-head matchups between the top teams:
Arsenal, Manchester City, Manchester United, Chelsea, and Liverpool.

This section includes:

- Scoring Analysis:
  Evaluates average goals to identify high-scoring rivalries.

- Match Intensity:
  Measures physical gameplay using fouls, yellow cards,
  and red cards.

- Performance Overview:
  Uses heatmaps to compare match behavior across key metrics
  such as goals, shots, fouls, and corners.

- Dominance Analysis:
  Evaluates how balanced or one-sided each matchup is based
  on win rate differences.

This section highlights how top teams interact with each other,
revealing patterns in competitiveness, playing style, and match dynamics.


------------------------------------------------------------
Summary
------------------------------------------------------------

This script completes the analytical pipeline of the project,
transforming structured SQL outputs into meaningful visual
insights.

It combines statistical analysis with visualization techniques
to provide a deeper understanding of football performance,
both at team level and matchup level.